title: Fecal Indicator Bacteria
text: Fecal Indicator Bacteria (FIB) used track concentrations pathogens surface waters may detrimental human health environment. Common indicators include concentrations E. coli, Enterococcus, Fecal Coliform number colony forming units (CFU) per 100 mL water. Many monitoring programs routinely measure FIB concentrations select locations. tbeptools package several functions importing reporting data. title: Water Quality Data
text: TBEP collaboration Tampa Bay Nitrogen Management Consortium (NMC) reports annually water quality conditions Tampa Bay Reasonable Assurance (RA) plan Florida Department Environmental Protection (FDEP). plan comprehensive approach managing nitrogen pollution Tampa Bay provides “reasonable assurance” designated uses waterbody segments bay maintained restored response potential nutrient impairments. Annual reports FDEP critical part plan tbeptools package includes functions facilitate reporting. functions previously described (e.g., show_wqmatrix()). title: Seagrass Transect Data

Shoot density reported number shoots per square meter corrected quadrat size entered raw data. Abundance reported numeric value 0 -5 Braun-Blanquet coverage estimates blade length cm. Change training argument FALSE download entire transect database. may take seconds. columns complete transect database describe crew (Crew), monitoring agency (MonitoringAgency), sample date (Date), transect name (Transect), meter location quadrat along transect (Site, m), depth site (Depth, cm), Seagrass species (Savspecies), distance seagrass edge transect (SeagrassEdge, m), seagrass variable (var), average value variable (aveval), standard deviation variable appropriate (sdval). raw, unformatted transect data preferred, use raw = TRUE argument read_transect().

title: Tampa Bay Nekton Index
text: Tampa Bay Nekton Index (TBNI) [1,2]) multimetric assessment method quantifies ecological health nekton community Tampa Bay. index provides complementary approach evaluating environmental condition supported assessment methods currently available Tampa Bay (e.g., water quality report card, Benthic index, etc.). tbeptools package includes several functions described import data required index, analyze data calculate metrics index scores, plot results view trends time. functions described detail . TBNI uses catch data Florida Fish Wildlife Conservation Commission (FWC) Fish Wildlife Research Institute’s (FWRI) Fisheries-Independent Monitoring (FIM) program. Catch results center-bag seine longest consistent record FIM database used develop TBNI. include counts taxa identification individuals caught near shore areas, generally early recruits, juveniles, smaller-bodied nekton. fish selected invertebrates identified lowest possible taxon (usually species), counted, subset measured. Current protocols established 1998 TBNI estimates unavailable prior date.

text: Metrics scores Tampa Bay Nekton Index can calculated using two functions. anlz_tbnimet() function calculates raw metrics anlz_tbniscr() function calculates scored metrics final TBNI score. functions use imported formatted FIM data input. TBNI includes five metrics sensitive stressor gradients provide unique information Nekton community response environmental conditions. metrics include: NumTaxa: Species richness BenthicTaxa: Species richness benthic taxa TaxaSelect: Number “selected” species (.e., commercially /recreationally important) NumGuilds: Number trophic guilds Shannon: Shannon Diversity (H) Raw metrics first calculated observed data scaled standard score 0 - 10 accounting expected relationships environmental gradients 5th/95th percentiles distributions. final TBNI score summed average scores ranging 0 - 100. raw metrics, scored metrics, final TBNI score returned anlz_tbniscr() function. five metrics chosen TBNI appropriate Tampa Bay dataset selected larger pool candidate metrics. potential metrics can calculated using anlz_tbnimet() function. metrics can used standalone assessments developing Nekton index outside Tampa Bay. argument = TRUE must used return metrics, otherwise selected five TBNI returned.

title: Analyze Fecal Indicator Bacteria categories over time by station or bay segment — anlz_fibmatrix
text: fibdata input data frame returned read_importfib, read_importentero, read_importwqp, see details yrrng numeric vector indicating min, max years include, defaults range years data, see details stas optional vector stations include, see details bay_segment optional vector bay segment names include, supercedes stas provided, see details indic character choice fecal indicator. Allowable options fcolif fecal coliform, entero Enterococcus. numeric column data frame must name. threshold optional numeric threshold calculate exceedances indicator bacteria choice. provided, defaults 400 fcolif 130 entero. lagyr numeric year lag calculate categories, see details subset_wetdry character, subset data frame wet dry samples defined wet_threshold temporal_window? Defaults "", subset. "wet" "dry" specified, anlz_fibwetdry called using specified parameters, data frame subsetted accordingly. precipdata input data frame returned read_importrain. columns : station, date (yyyy-mm-dd), rain (inches). object catchprecip data 1995-2023 select Enterococcus stations. NULL, defaults catchprecip. temporal_window numeric; required subset_wetdry "". number days precipitation summed (1 = day sample ; 2 = day sample + day ; etc.) wet_threshold numeric; required subset_wetdry "". inches accumulated defined temporal window, sample defined 'wet' time period warn logical print warnings stations insufficient data, default TRUE

title: Analyze Fecal Indicator Bacteria categories over time by station or bay segment — anlz_fibmatrix
text: tibble object FIB summaries year station including columns estimated geometric mean fecal coliform Enterococcus concentrations (gmean), proportion samples exceeding 400 CFU / 100 mL (fecal coliform) 130 CFU / 100 mL (Enterococcus) (exced), count samples (cnt), category indicating letter outcome based proportion exceedences (cat).  Results can summarized bay segment bay_segment NULL input data read_importentero.

title: Analyze Fecal Indicator Bacteria categories over time by station or bay segment — anlz_fibmatrix
text: function used create output plotting matrix stoplight graphic FIB categories station.  output can also summarized bay segment bay_segment NULL input data read_importentero. latter case, stas argument ignored stations within subsegment watershed used evaluate FIB categories. station (bay segment) year combination categorized based likelihood fecal indicator bacteria concentrations exceeding threshold given year.  fecal coliform, default threshold 400 CFU / 100 mL given year (using Fecal Coliform, fcolif fibdata).  Enterococcus, default threshold 130 CFU / 100 mL.  proportions categorized , B, C, D, E (Microbial Water Quality Assessment MWQA categories) corresponding colors, breakpoints category <10%, 10-30%, 30-50%, 50-75%, >75% (right-closed).  default, results year based right-centered window uses previous two years current year calculate probabilities using monthly samples (lagyr = 3). See show_fibmatrix additional details. yrrng can specified several ways.  yrrng = NULL, year range data selected changes chosen.  User-defined values minimum maximum years can also used, minimum maximum can specified, e.g., yrrng = c(2000, 2010) yrrng = c(2000, NA).  latter case, maximum year defined data. default stations fecal coliform data used TBEP report #05-13 (https://drive.google.com/file/d/1MZnK3cMzV7LRg6dTbCKX8AOZU0GNurJJ/view) Hillsborough River Basin Management Action Plan (BMAP) subbasins bay_segment NULL input data read_importfib.  include Blackwater Creek (WBID 1482, EPC stations 143, 108), Baker Creek (WBID 1522C, EPC station 107), Lake Thonotosassa (WBID 1522B, EPC stations 135, 118), Flint Creek (WBID 1522A, EPC station 148), Lower Hillsborough River (WBID 1443E, EPC stations 105, 152, 137).  stations can plotted using stas argument. Input read_importwqp Manatee County (21FLMANA_WQX) FIB data can also used.  function tested organizations.

title: Import data from the Water Quality Portal — read_importwqp
text: function retrieves data Water Quality Portal API (https://www.waterqualitydata.us/) selected counties around Tampa Bay watershed. type data returned defined type argument either "wq" "fib" water quality Fecal Indicator Bacteria data, respectively. org argument retrieves data specific organization. Valid entries org include "21FLCOSP_WQX" (City St. Petersburg), "21FLDOH_WQX" (Florida Department Health), "21FLHILL_WQX" (Hillsborough County), "21FLMANA_WQX" (Manatee County), "21FLPASC_WQX" (Pasco County), "21FLPDEM_WQX" (Pinellas County), "21FLPOLK_WQX" (Polk County), "21FLTPA_WQX" (Florida Department Environmental Protection, Southwest District).  naming convention follows Organization ID Water Quality Portal. function fetches results station metadata, combines formats using read_formwqp function, returns processed data data frame.  Parameters specific type argument.

title: Plot a matrix of Fecal Indicator Bacteria categories over time by station or bay segment — show_fibmatrix
text: matrix color codes years stations based likelihood fecal indicator bacteria concentrations exceeding 400 CFU / 100 mL Fecal Coliform 130 CFU / 100 mL Enterococcus.  Bay segments used instead stations bay_segment NULL input data read_importentero.  likelihoods categorized , B, C, D, E (Microbial Water Quality Assessment MWQA categories) corresponding colors, breakpoints category <10%, 10-30%, 30-50%, 50-75%, >75% (right-closed). default, results year based right-centered window uses previous two years current year calculate probabilities monthly samples (lagyr = 3).  Methods rationale categorization scheme provided Florida Department Environmental Protection, Figure 8 document http://publicfiles.dep.state.fl.us/DEAR/BMAP/Tampa/MST%20Report/Fecal%20BMAP%20DST%20Final%20Report%20--%20June%202008.pdf Morrison et al. 2009 BASIS 5 proceedings. default stations fecal coliform data used TBEP report #05-13 (https://drive.google.com/file/d/1MZnK3cMzV7LRg6dTbCKX8AOZU0GNurJJ/view) Hillsborough River Basin Management Action Plan (BMAP) subbasins bay_segment NULL input data read_importfib.  include Blackwater Creek (WBID 1482, EPC stations 143, 108), Baker Creek (WBID 1522C, EPC station 107), Lake Thonotosassa (WBID 1522B, EPC stations 135, 118), Flint Creek (WBID 1522A, EPC station 148), Lower Hillsborough River (WBID 1443E, EPC stations 105, 152, 137).  stations can plotted using stas argument.
